removeTypes

void removeTypes()

delete

void delete()
Entirely deletes this individual in the ontology it is part of. More precisely, it deletes all statements that refer to it, that is, where it occurs as either statement-subject or statement-object.

No matter if this individual is anonymous or not, the backing resource still exists - actually, just its URI respectively anon identifier, but no statements. As such, it can be still used, for instance, to add or set properties, which will add this individual back to the ontology referred to by OWLEntity.getOntology().

toRDF

java.lang.String toRDF(boolean printRDFtag,
                       boolean inlineNamespaces)
Return the RDF/XML representation of this individual. The returned RDF/XML is supposed to be a nested RDF statement which is the b-node closure of the individual.

Parameters:
printRDFtag - If false the enclosing <rdf:RDF> tag will be omitted.
inlineNamespaces - If true namespaces declared within the <rdf:RDF> tag wont get lost but occur in-line in the result (good to quote whole expression). This parameter is only relevant if withRDFtag is false.
Returns:
The RDF/XML representation of this individual.
